DTSTAMP:20260325T180459
CREATED:20260206T233704Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260326T012214Z
UID:10012810-1776168000-1776173400@www.connectmatsu.org
SUMMARY:Organic Gardening: Build Your Soil's Microbe Bank
DESCRIPTION:This is an in-person Organic Gardening class that meets at Mat-Su College in the Snodgrass Hall Building (SGH)\, first floor in Room 117. This course meets for 1 day only from 12:00-1:30 p.m. Cost is $25. \nYour soil may have all the minerals in the world–but they are useless if your garden lacks the microorganisms to deliver them to your plants. But how? Which ones? Snatch up this practical guidance that will have our soil “teaming’ with helpful microbes! This course meets for a one 90-mintue session. The instructor presents the material via a slideshow and with hands-on demonstrations.
URL:https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/organic-gardening-build-your-soils-microbe-bank/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.connectmatsu.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/MSC-Soil-Microbe-Bank.jpg
END:VEVENT
